PC Number Date Chapter Bill Dept
 1998-12511998-07-150,  ,  ,  FAIT, 
PrecisAppointment of DONALD McMASTER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Côte d'Ivoire; JANET GRAHAM as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Ghana; JOHN SCHRAM as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia; DAVID HUTTON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Hellenic Republic; HAIG SARAFIAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Lebanese Republic; JOHN NOBLE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Swiss Confederation; RICHARD KOHLER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Federative Republic of Brazil; DAVID COLLINS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Romania, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Bulgaria, with residence in Bucharest; and with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Moldova, with residence in Bucharest; JEAN-PAUL HUBERT as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Argentine Republic, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Paraguay, with residence in Buenos Aires; MARIE-ANDRÉE BEAUCHEMIN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Arab Republic of Egypt; ALLAN STEWART as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Venezuela; MICHÈLE LEVESQUE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Senegal, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Cape Verde, with residence in Dakar; and with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Islamic Republic of Mauritania, with residence in Dakar; and with concurrent accreditation as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Gambia, with residence in Dakar; DEREK FRASER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Ukraine; BRIAN NORTHGRAVE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Eastern Republic of Uruguay; GERALD K. CAMPBELL as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Kenya, with concurrent accreditation as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Uganda, with residence in Nairobi; with concurrent accreditation as Permanent Representative of Canada to the United Nations Centre for Human Settlements, with residence in Nairobi; and with concurrent accreditation as Permanent Representative of Canada to the United Nations Environment Program; JOHN KNEALE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Ecuador; MARK BAILEY as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Morocco; ARTHUR C. PERRON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Korea; and CLAUDE BAILLARGEON as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Cameroon. . . . . .
Attachments
precis:
